The paper discusses visual odometry approaches and their evaluation on different datasets, which falls under the robotics (cs.RO) and computer vision (cs.CV) sub-categories. The use of machine learning techniques to improve the performance metrics of visual SLAM systems suggests a possible fit for the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The proposal of a real-time approach for semi-dense visual odometry also suggests a possible fit for the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and systems and control (cs.SY) sub-categories.
